ian-American sculptor and furniture designer (d. 1978) \n*  1915   &ndash; [[Jo\u017ea Horvat]], Croatian writer (d. 2012) \n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Davie Fulton]], Canadian lawyer, judge, and politician (d. 2000)\n*[[1917]] &ndash; [[David Hare (artist)|David Hare]], American Surrealist artist, sculptor, photographer and painter (d. 1992)\n*[[1918]] &ndash; [[G\u00fcnther Rall]], German general and pilot (d. 2009)\n*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Marion Hutton]], American singer and actress (d. 1987)\n*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Alfred Peet]], Dutch-American businessman, founded [[Peet's Coffee & Tea]] (d. 2007)\n*  1920   &ndash; [[Boris Vian]], French author and playwright (d. 1959)\n*[[1922]] &ndash; [[Kiyoshi Yamashita]], Japanese painter (d. 1971)\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[Val Logsdon Fitch]], American physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2015)\n*[[1924]] &ndash; [[Judith Jones]], American literary and cookbook editor (d. 2017)\n*  1925   &ndash; [[Bob Lanier (politician)|Bob Lanier]], American lawyer, banker, and politician, 58th [[List of mayors of Houston|Mayor of Houston]] (d. 2014)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Marques Haynes]], American basketball player (d. 2015)\n*[[1927]] &ndash; [[Claude Laydu]], Belgian-French actor, producer, and screenwriter (d. 2011)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Paul Wunderlich]],  German painter, sculptor and graphic artist (d. 2010)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Sara Montiel]], Spanish actress (d. 2013)\n*  1928   &ndash; [[James Earl Ray]], American criminal; assassin of Martin Luther King Jr. (d. 1998)\n*[[1929]] &ndash; [[Sam Steiger]], American journalist and politician (d. 2012)\n*[[1930]] &ndash; [[S\u00e1ndor Iharos]], Hungarian runner (d. 1996)\n*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Georges Dor]], Canadian author, playwright, and composer (d. 2001)\n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[Marcia Falkender, Baroness Falkender]], English politician (d. 2019)\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Udupi Ramachandra Rao]], Indian physicist and engineer (d. 2017)\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Perunchithi