ota]], Japanese physician and microbiologist, invented [[Yakult]] (b. 1899)\n*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Konstantin Chernenko]], Russian soldier and politician, 8th [[List of heads of state of the Soviet Union|Head of State of The Soviet Union]] (b. 1911)\n*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Bob Nieman]], American baseball player and scout (b. 1927)\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Ray Milland]], Welsh-American actor and director (b. 1905)\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[Andy Gibb]], Manx-Australian singer-songwriter and actor (b. 1958)\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Kermit Beahan]], American colonel and pilot (b. 1918)\n*[[1990]] &ndash; [[Pat McDonald (actress)|Pat McDonald]], Australian actress (b. 1921)\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Giorgos Zampetas]], Greek [[bouzouki]] player and composer (b. 1925)\n*[[1995]] &ndash; [[Agep\u00ea]], Brazilian singer/composer (b. [[1942]])\n*[[1996]] &ndash; [[Ross Hunter]], American film producer (b. 1926)\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[LaVern Baker]], American singer and actress (b. 1929)\n*[[1998]] &ndash; [[Lloyd Bridges]], American actor and director (b. 1913)\n*[[1999]] &ndash; [[Oswaldo Guayasam\u00edn]], Ecuadorian painter and sculptor (b. 1919)\n*[[2001]] &ndash; [[Massimo Morsello]], Italian singer-songwriter (b. 1958)\n*[[2004]] &ndash; [[Renos Apostolidis]], Greek philologist, author, and critic (b. 1924)\n*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Dave Allen (comedian)|Dave Allen]], Irish-English comedian, actor, and screenwriter (b. 1936)\n*[[2006]] &ndash; [[Anna Moffo]], American soprano (b. 1932)\n*[[2007]] &ndash; [[Ernie Ladd]], American football player and wrestler (b. 1938)\n*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Muhammad Sayyid Tantawy]], Egyptian scholar and academic (b. 1928)\n*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Corey Haim]], Canadian actor (b. 1971)<ref>{{cite web |title='Lost Boys' star Corey Haim dies at 38 - CNN.com |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2010/SHOWBIZ/Movies/03/10/corey.haim.obit/index.html |website=www.cnn.com |accessdate=March 10, 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[2011]] &ndash; [[Bill Blackbeard]], American author and illustrat