 Island elections, 2018#Lieutenant Governor|2018-09-12]]\n|{{No|Lost}}\n|{{No|49.2%}}\n|{{No|Did not qualify}}\n|{{No|N/A}}\n|}\n\n====U.S. Senate ====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">Candidate</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">State</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">Office</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">Primary date</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">Primary result</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\"><abbr title=\"Primary vote share\">%</abbr></span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\">General result</span>\n!bgcolor=teal |<span style=\"color:black;\"><abbr title=\"General vote share\">%</abbr></span>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|{{sortname|Deedra|Abboud}}\n|{{flagicon|Arizona}} Arizona\n|[[List of United States Senators from Arizona|U.S. Senator from Arizona]]\n|[[United States Senate election in Arizona, 2018#Democratic primary|2018-08-28]]\n|{{No|Lost}}\n|{{No|19.5%}}\n|{{No|Did not qualify}}\n|{{No|N/A}}\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|{{sortname|Alison|Hartson}}\n|{{flagicon|California}} California\n|[[List of United States Senators from California|U.S. Senator from California]]\n|[[United States Senate election in California, 2018|2018-06-05]]\n|{{No|Lost}}\n|{{No|2.1%}}\n|{{No|Did not qualify}}\n|{{No|N/A}}\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|{{sortname|Kerri Evelyn|Harris}}\n|{{flagicon|Delaware}} Delaware\n|[[List of United States Senators from Delaware|U.S. Senator from Delaware]]\n|[[United States Senate election in Delaware, 2018|2018-09-06]]\n|{{No|Lost}}\n|{{No|35.4%}}\n|{{No|Did not qualify}}\n|{{No|N/A}}\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|{{sortname|Paula Jean|Swearengin}}\n|{{flagicon|West Virginia}} West Virginia\n|[[List of United States Senators from West Virginia|U.S. Senator from West Virginia]]\n|[[United States Senate election in West Virginia, 2018#Democratic primary|2018-05-08]]\n|{{No|Lost